                  <Text layoutX="55.0" layoutY="232.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Animation has existed in some form for centuries, from traditional shadow puppetry in Asian cultures—including the Philippine karakol and sinakulo plays—to the flipbooks and early motion toys of the 1800s. These storytelling forms laid the foundation for modern animation techniques." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
