                  <Text layoutX="55.0" layoutY="656.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="With the rise of digital tools in the 2000s, animation became more accessible. No longer confined to drawing each frame by hand, animators began using software to streamline workflows and improve visual quality. Today, students in the Philippines can explore animation using programs like Adobe Animate, Blender, and Toon Boom Harmony—many of which are free or available through schools. This shift made animation a practical skill for young Filipinos interested in ICT, graphic design, or storytelling." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
